# Commenting

- Comments are code: write them only to explain a decision, capture non-obvious context,
  or cite a reference — not to restate what the code already says.
- Document non-obvious design/architectural decisions at the source (docstring, comment,
  or adjacent README): the WHY, so a future reader understands it without digging through
  git history.
- No commented-out or dead code — delete it; version control remembers.
